         Hmmm....I always thought the main focus of a thread would be the question put forth by the person who started it. His/her question was: </P><P>Does anyone know what changes,to innate regen, EQ Developer board is referring to? They say it has been changed and the points spent on it will be refunded. </P><P>Which is exactly what I answered.</P><P>So I don't really get what point you're trying to make. Did you mean that (1) I failed to answer Malthor's question, or (2) I didn't answer your speculation?</P><P>If it's (1), then did you miss the use of the phrase "a previous change to Innate Regeneration" in the quote you repeated twice? The refund is for a change made previously to Innate Regen, not one which will be made in the patch this week. As there has only been 1 change made previously to Innate Regen, I don't think I missed the focus of Malthus's question.</P><P>If it's (2), then I truly apologise for not answering your query. I hadn't realised that you wanted an answer. I doubt that VI will let everyone who spent 3 points in Innate Regen ignore the fact that they will now have less than 6 points in their General skills. There will almost certainly be coding put in place that will not allow you to spend any more points if the prerequisites (however indirect) are not fulfilled. Using your example, having 6 points in General is a prerequisite for getting Arch abilities and having 12 points in Arch is a prerequisite for getting Class abilities. So, having 6 points in General is an indirect prerequisite for getting Class abilities. Hope that suitably furnishes you with my opinion on that idea.</P><P>On a related note though, VI is likely to muck up point refunds if they make it an automated proccess. I hope that they will make it a 'manual' process where we can untrain these skills if we want to.</P><P>Tenaiya Soulscorcher<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
